0:["psdu3ijGrdNaEXr5inVpP",[[["",{"children":["blog",{"children":[["slug","what-to-expect-from-professional-audio-engineering","d"],{"children":["__PAGE__?{\"slug\":\"what-to-expect-from-professional-audio-engineering\"}",{}]}]}]},"$undefined","$undefined",true],["",{"children":["blog",{"children":[["slug","what-to-expect-from-professional-audio-engineering","d"],{"children":["__PAGE__",{},[["$L1",[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"Article\",\"headline\":\"What to Expect from a Professional Audio Engineer\",\"description\":\"Audio is half of video and most of a live event. Here's what a professional audio engineer brings to a project and why it matters more than people realize.\",\"datePublished\":\"2026-03-15\",\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Gulf Coast Production Network\",\"url\":\"https://gulfcoastproductionnetwork.com\"},\"mainEntityOfPage\":\"https://gulfcoastproductionnetwork.com/blog/what-to-expect-from-professional-audio-engineering\"}"}}],["$","div",null,{"className":"pt-16 min-h-screen","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 pt-12 pb-8","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"text-teal text-xs font-condensed tracking-widest uppercase hover:underline mb-6 inline-block","children":"← Back to Guides"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-3 mb-4","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-condensed text-[10px] tracking-widest uppercase bg-teal/10 text-teal border border-teal/20 px-2 py-0.5 rounded","children":"Industry Basics"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-muted text-xs","children":"5 min read"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-muted text-xs","children":"·"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-muted text-xs","children":"March 14, 2026"}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl tracking-widest text-white leading-tight mb-6","children":"What to Expect from a Professional Audio Engineer"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted text-lg leading-relaxed border-l-2 border-teal pl-4","children":"Audio is half of video and most of a live event. Here's what a professional audio engineer brings to a project and why it matters more than people realize."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"border-t border-white/[0.06] mb-10"}]}],["$","article",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 pb-16","children":[[["$","p","0",{"className":"text-white/75 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["There's a saying in production that audiences will forgive bad video before they forgive bad audio. It sounds counterintuitive, but it's true. Shaky handheld footage feels documentary and real. Distorted, muddy, or poorly balanced audio makes everything feel amateur — and it's often the reason viewers stop watching."]}],["$","p","1",{"className":"text-white/75 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["A professional audio engineer is one of the most underrated hires you can make for any production or live event."]}],["$","h2","2",{"className":"font-display text-2xl tracking-widest text-white mt-10 mb-4","children":"What an Audio Engineer Does"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"text-white/75 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["The role varies depending on the context, but broadly, an audio engineer is responsible for capturing, mixing, and delivering clean, balanced sound."]}],["$","p","4",{"className":"text-white/75 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"text-white font-semibold","children":"On a video production"}],", the audio engineer handles microphone placement (lavaliers on talent, boom mics for ambient coverage), monitors the audio in real time, and flags problems before they become unusable footage. They work to eliminate background noise, room echo, and the dozens of small audio issues that kill otherwise good footage."]}],["$","p","5",{"className":"text-white/75 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"text-white font-semibold","children":"At a live event"}],", the audio engineer manages the entire sound system — speakers, monitors, microphones, mixing board. They set levels for each input, balance the mix during the performance or presentation, and respond in real time to changes on stage. A good live sound engineer is essentially invisible — the audience just hears everything clearly."]}],["$","p","6",{"className":"text-white/75 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["",["$","strong","1",{"className":"text-white font-semibold","children":"In post-production"}],", an audio engineer cleans up recorded dialogue, balances music and sound effects, and delivers the final mix to whatever specifications the project requires."]}],["$","h2","7",{"className":"font-display text-2xl tracking-widest text-white mt-10 mb-4","children":"What Separates Good Audio from Great Audio"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"text-white/75 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["Most people can't articulate exactly why some productions sound better than others, but they feel it immediately. Great audio has:"]}],["$","ul","9",{"className":"list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"text-white/75 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":"**Clarity** — Speech is intelligible without effort"}],["$","li","1",{"className":"text-white/75 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":"**Balance** — No single element dominates unnaturally"}],["$","li","2",{"className":"text-white/75 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":"**Presence** — The sound feels like it exists in a real space"}],["$","li","3",{"className":"text-white/75 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":"**Consistency** — Levels don't jump or drop unexpectedly"}]]}],["$","p","10",{"className":"text-white/75 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["Achieving this requires both technical skill and a trained ear. It requires knowing when a microphone placement is going to cause problems before the camera rolls, and knowing how to fix issues in real time."]}],["$","h2","11",{"className":"font-display text-2xl tracking-widest text-white mt-10 mb-4","children":"When to Hire a Dedicated Audio Engineer"}],["$","p","12",{"className":"text-white/75 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["For simple interview setups or solo documentary work, the camera operator often handles audio. But for anything with complexity — multiple speakers, live music, a large venue, broadcast delivery, or a corporate event where audio failure is not an option — a dedicated audio engineer is essential."]}],["$","p","13",{"className":"text-white/75 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["On the Gulf Coast, events ranging from festival stages to corporate conferences to film productions regularly require audio professionals with serious live and studio experience. If sound quality matters to your project, it's worth finding someone who specializes in it."]}]],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-teal/10 to-transparent border border-teal/20 rounded-2xl p-8 text-center","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"font-display text-2xl tracking-widest mb-3","children":"Find a Professional on the Gulf Coast"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted text-sm mb-6","children":"Browse verified media professionals available for your next project — from Tallahassee to New Orleans."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/browse","className":"btn-teal font-display tracking-widest px-6 py-2","children":"Browse Pros"}],["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/post-job","className":"btn-outline font-display tracking-widest px-6 py-2","children":"Post a Job"}]]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-navy2 border-t border-white/[0.06] py-12 px-4","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-6xl mx-auto","children":[["$","h2",null,{"classN